Dialogue: 0,0:00:01.87,0:00:03.54,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Thanks, Professor.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:04.00,0:00:04.79,DCMain,AGASA,0000,0000,0000,,Sure.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:10.31,0:00:14.94,DCMain,HAIBARA,0000,0000,0000,,What was Kudo-kun doing here \Nso early on a Sunday morning?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:15.41,0:00:18.24,DCMain,AGASA,0000,0000,0000,,He came to get his phone that I repaired.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:18.52,0:00:23.46,DCMain,AGASA,0000,0000,0000,,I told him you'd bring it \Nto the soccer game today,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:23.46,0:00:26.32,DCMain,AGASA,0000,0000,0000,,but he said he'd come get it right away.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:26.32,0:00:27.71,DCMain,HAIBARA,0000,0000,0000,,Huh...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:32.60,0:00:35.38,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Yikes! Seventeen received messages?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:33.01,0:00:35.89,DCNote,TEXT,0000,0000,0000,,Media Browser Messages Calls Folder
Dialogue: 0,0:00:37.51,0:00:38.18,Texts,TEXT,0000,0000,0000,,Ran \NSchool Trip  Answer my messages \NRan \NSchool Trip  We're going to Kyoto! \NRan \NSchool Trip  Answer my messages \NRan \NSchool Trip  Is your phone broken?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:38.19,0:00:38.94,Texts,TEXT,0000,0000,0000,,Ran \NSchool Trip  We're going to Kyoto! \NRan \NSchool Trip  Answer my messages \NRan \NSchool Trip  Is your phone broken? \NRan \N School Trip  Answer your messages!!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:38.40,0:00:40.13,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,They're all from Ran?!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:38.94,0:00:39.68,Texts,TEXT,0000,0000,0000,,Ran \NSchool Trip  Answer my messages \NRan \NSchool Trip  Is your phone broken? \NRan \N School Trip  Answer your messages!! \NRan \NRan \NSchool Trip  Let me know if there's \Nanywhere you want to go in Kyoto
Dialogue: 0,0:00:39.69,0:00:40.44,Texts,TEXT,0000,0000,0000,,Ran \NSchool Trip  Is your phone broken? \NRan \N School Trip  Answer your messages!! \NRan \NSchool Trip  Let me know if there's \Nanywhere you want to go in Kyoto \NRan \NSchool Trip  I signed you up for our group!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:40.44,0:00:41.02,Texts,TEXT,0000,0000,0000,,Ran \NSchool Trip  Answer your messages!! \NRan \NSchool Trip  Let me know if there's \Nanywhere you want to go in Kyoto \NRan \NSchool Trip  I signed you up for our group! \NRan \NSchool Trip  We're going to Kyoto! \NWill you be able to make it?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:41.93,0:00:44.03,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Time is the y-axis, and I'm the x-axis!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:44.03,0:00:46.10,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Inscribing love and cases \Nwith deductive reasoning!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:46.25,0:00:48.19,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Ran's messages are about the school trip!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:48.19,0:00:49.77,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,I wish I could respond right away!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:50.07,0:00:51.71,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Always determining the one truth
Dialogue: 0,0:00:51.71,0:00:53.56,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,with the body of a child \Nand the mind of an adult,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:53.56,0:00:56.03,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,his name is Detective Conan!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:37.01,0:02:43.01,DCEpTitle,EPTITLE,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(397,1)}The Heartfelt Strap \N(Part One)
Dialogue: 0,0:02:37.54,0:02:40.74,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,“The Heartfelt Strap, Part One!”
Dialogue: 0,0:03:07.73,0:03:09.58,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Yes!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:17.96,0:03:21.47,DCItalic,ANNOUNCE,0000,0000,0000,,Next stop, Beika. Beika.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:22.62,0:03:24.83,DCMain,GENTA,0000,0000,0000,,That was amazing!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:24.83,0:03:27.82,DCMain,GENTA,0000,0000,0000,,Did you see Hide's long shot?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:27.82,0:03:28.87,DCMain,BOTH,0000,0000,0000,,Yes!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:28.87,0:03:31.48,DCMain,MITSUHIKO,0000,0000,0000,,I can't believe he scored from that far away!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:31.72,0:03:35.61,DCMain,AYUMI,0000,0000,0000,,BIG Osaka's goalie was surprised, too!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:35.61,0:03:38.65,DCMain,HAIBARA,0000,0000,0000,,What? A school trip?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:38.65,0:03:42.99,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, for Teitan High School. So, you know...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:42.99,0:03:45.80,DCMain,HAIBARA,0000,0000,0000,,You want to use the APTX4869 antidote
Dialogue: 0,0:03:45.80,0:03:48.66,DCMain,HAIBARA,0000,0000,0000,,to restore your body so \Nyou can participate, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:48.66,0:03:51.66,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,I knew you'd understand, Haibara!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:51.84,0:03:52.66,DCMain,HAIBARA,0000,0000,0000,,No.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:53.03,0:03:53.64,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:55.44,0:03:58.50,DCMain,HAIBARA,0000,0000,0000,,The effects of the antidote \Nare still only temporary.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:58.50,0:04:01.85,DCMain,HAIBARA,0000,0000,0000,,If you continuously take it in order to remain \Nin your original body during the school trip,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:01.85,0:04:05.55,DCMain,HAIBARA,0000,0000,0000,,there's no telling what kind \Nof side effects there could be.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:06.00,0:04:08.18,DCMain,HAIBARA,0000,0000,0000,,And besides, when you went to London...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:09.28,0:04:10.67,DCItalic,HAIBARA,0000,0000,0000,,Your passport.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:10.67,0:04:11.31,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:11.84,0:04:13.40,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:13.81,0:04:16.44,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, crap! I totally forgot!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:16.83,0:04:19.32,DCItalic,HAIBARA,0000,0000,0000,,There is one way you could go.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:19.56,0:04:22.62,DCItalic,AGASA,0000,0000,0000,,You've got Ai-kun's fantastic \Nidea to thank for this.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:22.62,0:04:24.95,DCItalic,SHINICHI,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah. I'm grateful.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:25.48,0:04:27.95,DCItalic,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,Conan-kun and the professor aren't coming.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:28.26,0:04:29.48,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Ran-neechan!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:30.13,0:04:31.20,DCItalic,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,Conan-kun?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:31.20,0:04:32.90,DCItalic,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,When did you get here?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:32.90,0:04:36.33,DCItalic,AGASA,0000,0000,0000,,Just now. You didn't notice?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:36.60,0:04:39.34,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,The effects of the medicine \Nwouldn't wear off,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:39.34,0:04:42.04,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,so I was stuck in the \Nbathroom for 30 minutes.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:44.29,0:04:45.22,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Hello?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:45.44,0:04:47.68,DCItalic,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,Sorry, Shinichi?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:47.68,0:04:48.80,DCItalic,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,It's me...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:49.09,0:04:49.70,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:50.11,0:04:52.68,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, crap! This is Shinichi's phone!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:56.15,0:05:00.19,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Can't hear you hear the \Nsound of Big Ben over here?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:00.50,0:05:02.69,DCItalic,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,Big Ben over here?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:04.03,0:05:06.70,DCItalic,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,You're here in London?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:07.11,0:05:10.76,DCItalic,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,Shinichi, you can't escape now!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:10.76,0:05:15.96,DCItalic,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,Now why don't you explain \Nwhat's going on, Shinichi?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:20.63,0:05:24.47,DCItalic,AGASA,0000,0000,0000,,Did he take the antidote \Nhe needed to return home?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:26.07,0:05:27.38,DCItalic,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,Shinichi?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:28.43,0:05:29.47,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:29.98,0:05:33.66,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Something came up. I can't make it anymore.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:34.55,0:05:37.46,DCItalic,AGASA,0000,0000,0000,,You'd better thank Ai-kun.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:37.46,0:05:38.38,DCItalic,SHINICHI,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:39.49,0:05:41.98,DCMain,HAIBARA,0000,0000,0000,,And the Shiragami case!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:42.48,0:05:44.66,DCItalic,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,I had a local doctor come.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:44.66,0:05:47.90,DCItalic,HATTORI,0000,0000,0000,,I told you, he's fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:47.90,0:05:48.96,DCItalic,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,But...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:02.78,0:06:05.09,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Haibara! What are you doing here?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:06.16,0:06:07.72,DCItalic,HAIBARA,0000,0000,0000,,There's no time to explain.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:08.09,0:06:10.34,DCItalic,HAIBARA,0000,0000,0000,,Take this immediately.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:12.41,0:06:14.39,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,I-Is this...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:14.61,0:06:15.47,DCItalic,HAIBARA,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:15.47,0:06:20.95,DCItalic,HAIBARA,0000,0000,0000,,It's a prototype antidote to the \NAPTX4869 that turned you into a child.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:20.95,0:06:23.57,DCItalic,HAIBARA,0000,0000,0000,,The same as the one you took yesterday.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:24.03,0:06:26.36,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Will it last 24 hours again?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:26.69,0:06:28.09,DCItalic,HAIBARA,0000,0000,0000,,You idiot.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:28.09,0:06:32.34,DCItalic,HAIBARA,0000,0000,0000,,Just as habitually consuming the \Nsame medicine reduces its effects,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:32.34,0:06:35.94,DCItalic,HAIBARA,0000,0000,0000,,your body has developed a \Nresistance to that medicine.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:35.94,0:06:40.00,DCItalic,HAIBARA,0000,0000,0000,,If you keep using it, its \Nduration decreases, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:40.00,0:06:41.94,DCItalic,HAIBARA,0000,0000,0000,,If you want to keep your identity hidden,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:41.94,0:06:46.14,DCItalic,HAIBARA,0000,0000,0000,,you'll have to say goodbye to \Nthem before its effects run out
Dialogue: 0,0:06:46.59,0:06:48.23,DCItalic,HAIBARA,0000,0000,0000,,and you turn back into Edogawa Conan.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:49.35,0:06:52.56,DCMain,HAIBARA,0000,0000,0000,,I've saved you countless \Ntimes with my quick wits
Dialogue: 0,0:06:52.56,0:06:55.48,DCMain,HAIBARA,0000,0000,0000,,when the effects of the medicine expired \Nand your identity was about to be discovered!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:55.48,0:06:57.28,DCMain,HAIBARA,0000,0000,0000,,You {\i1}still{\i0} haven't learned your lesson?!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:57.28,0:06:58.64,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Calm down.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:59.06,0:07:02.23,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,I know you're upset because BIG Osaka lost,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:02.23,0:07:08.54,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,but you were in a great mood since you \Ngot to meet Higo-san in the stands,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:08.54,0:07:11.53,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,who was out of the game due to an injury.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:11.76,0:07:15.63,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,I even wore a BIG hat today \Nand cheered for them.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:15.63,0:07:18.57,DCMain,HAIBARA,0000,0000,0000,,You shouldn't have done that.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:19.08,0:07:20.41,DCMain,HAIBARA,0000,0000,0000,,You're the reason they lost!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:20.84,0:07:24.44,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,She's still upset over the loss.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:26.55,0:07:28.29,DCMain,MITSUHIKO,0000,0000,0000,,It's so shiny.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:28.29,0:07:29.92,DCMain,GENTA,0000,0000,0000,,I just polished it yesterday.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:30.79,0:07:33.99,DCMain,HAIBARA,0000,0000,0000,,Either way, give up on that school trip.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:39.27,0:07:42.98,DCItalic,DRIVER,0000,0000,0000,,We apologize for the sudden \Nstop due to a red light.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:42.98,0:07:45.22,DCMain,GENTA,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}Ouch...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:43.71,0:07:46.48,DCItalic,DRIVER,0000,0000,0000,,The doors will open once we've confirmed \Nit's safe to exit the train.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:46.85,0:07:48.98,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Are you okay, Haibara?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:49.99,0:07:51.53,DCMain,HAIBARA,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, I'm fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:52.01,0:07:53.30,DCMain,HAIBARA,0000,0000,0000,,Thanks.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:53.30,0:07:54.90,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,You're not hurt, are you?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:54.90,0:07:55.85,DCMain,HAIBARA,0000,0000,0000,,No.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:56.35,0:07:58.20,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,You scraped your knee!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:58.72,0:08:00.01,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Do you need me to support you?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:01.57,0:08:03.19,DCItalic,ANNOUNCE,0000,0000,0000,,The doors are opening.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:04.29,0:08:07.09,DCMain,HAIBARA,0000,0000,0000,,Being nice to me won't work.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:08.45,0:08:09.50,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Really?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:12.09,0:08:14.59,DCMain,AGASA,0000,0000,0000,,You met Higo in the stands, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:14.89,0:08:16.76,DCMain,AGASA,0000,0000,0000,,That's great.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:16.76,0:08:19.85,DCMain,AYUMI,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah. He was really cool.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:20.14,0:08:23.13,DCMain,AYUMI,0000,0000,0000,,Ai-chan was blushing.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:23.13,0:08:25.76,DCMain,MITSUHIKO,0000,0000,0000,,We even got to talk with him a little.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:25.76,0:08:26.77,DCMain,HAIBARA,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:26.77,0:08:30.80,DCMain,AYUMI,0000,0000,0000,,And you got a Higo-san phone strap.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:30.80,0:08:32.86,DCMain,MITSUHIKO,0000,0000,0000,,It was the last one.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:33.40,0:08:35.36,DCMain,HAIBARA,0000,0000,0000,,I was very lucky.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:36.72,0:08:39.12,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Haibara's mood is improving.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:39.12,0:08:43.66,DCMain,GENTA,0000,0000,0000,,BIG might've won if \NHigo-san were in the game.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:46.28,0:08:48.13,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Genta!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:48.48,0:08:51.85,DCMain,MITSUHIKO,0000,0000,0000,,Come to think of it, I got a photo of it.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:51.85,0:08:53.08,DCMain,MITSUHIKO,0000,0000,0000,,I'll show you.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:53.08,0:08:54.76,DCMain,AGASA,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, please.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:55.25,0:08:56.94,DCMain,MITSUHIKO,0000,0000,0000,,Wait, what?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:56.94,0:08:57.89,DCMain,AYUMI,0000,0000,0000,,What's wrong?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:58.40,0:09:00.71,DCMain,MITSUHIKO,0000,0000,0000,,It's recording.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:00.71,0:09:02.68,DCMain,AYUMI,0000,0000,0000,,What? You're right.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:02.68,0:09:04.48,DCMain,GENTA,0000,0000,0000,,Since when?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:04.48,0:09:07.42,DCMain,MITSUHIKO,0000,0000,0000,,It seems to have started \Nwhile we were on the train.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:07.42,0:09:08.44,DCMain,BOTH,0000,0000,0000,,What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:08.44,0:09:09.65,DCMain,AYUMI,0000,0000,0000,,That long?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:09.98,0:09:15.78,DCMain,MITSUHIKO,0000,0000,0000,,I seem to have pressed the button when \NI made sure I hadn't dropped my phone
Dialogue: 0,0:09:15.78,0:09:17.66,DCMain,MITSUHIKO,0000,0000,0000,,after the train suddenly stopped and we fell.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:17.89,0:09:21.50,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,It's because you keep yours in \Nthe rear pocket of your pants.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:21.50,0:09:24.06,DCMain,AYUMI,0000,0000,0000,,Why were you keeping it there?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:24.06,0:09:27.70,DCMain,MITSUHIKO,0000,0000,0000,,I saw Haibara-san doing it, so I copied her.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:29.28,0:09:31.47,DCMain,AYUMI,0000,0000,0000,,Ai-chan, is your phone okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:31.47,0:09:34.05,DCMain,HAIBARA,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah. It's right here in—
Dialogue: 0,0:09:38.93,0:09:40.01,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,What's wrong, Haibara?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:41.21,0:09:42.76,DCMain,MITSUHIKO,0000,0000,0000,,It's gone.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:43.25,0:09:48.69,DCMain,MITSUHIKO,0000,0000,0000,,The Higo-san strap I attached \Nto my phone is gone!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:49.06,0:09:50.11,DCMain,AYUMI,0000,0000,0000,,No way!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:50.11,0:09:51.43,DCMain,GENTA,0000,0000,0000,,Seriously?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:51.43,0:09:54.37,DCMain,MITSUHIKO,0000,0000,0000,,You mean the very last one you got, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:56.24,0:09:59.95,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sure you'll be able \Nto buy one online soon.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:00.58,0:10:02.29,DCMain,HAIBARA,0000,0000,0000,,I can't!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:02.29,0:10:02.87,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:02.87,0:10:05.37,DCMain,HAIBARA,0000,0000,0000,,That strap is special. Today, Higo-san...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:06.67,0:10:07.53,DCItalic,HIGO,0000,0000,0000,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:08.74,0:10:09.71,DCItalic,HIGO,0000,0000,0000,,It's you.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:11.83,0:10:15.36,DCItalic,HIGO,0000,0000,0000,,You're the girl from the \Ncase at Asuka-san's restaurant.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:16.51,0:10:17.34,DCItalic,HAIBARA,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:18.64,0:10:21.48,DCItalic,HIGO,0000,0000,0000,,Huh. They're selling that now?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:26.78,0:10:29.21,DCItalic,HIGO,0000,0000,0000,,It's actually cute, unlike me.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:31.92,0:10:33.52,DCMain,HAIBARA,0000,0000,0000,,And then he touched it!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:33.91,0:10:37.69,DCMain,HAIBARA,0000,0000,0000,,There's only one strap \Nlike that in the world!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:47.70,0:10:48.68,DCMain,AYUMI,0000,0000,0000,,Ai-chan?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:49.20,0:10:52.00,DCMain,MITSUHIKO,0000,0000,0000,,But where did we lose it?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:52.00,0:10:54.34,DCMain,GENTA,0000,0000,0000,,Probably when we fell on the train.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:55.59,0:10:59.89,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Mitsuhiko, let me see that video you \Naccidentally recorded on your phone.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:59.89,0:11:01.26,DCMain,MITSUHIKO,0000,0000,0000,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:03.93,0:11:06.26,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Are you okay, Haibara?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:08.00,0:11:10.63,DCMain,AYUMI,0000,0000,0000,,That man next to the train doors...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:10.63,0:11:12.68,DCMain,MITSUHIKO,0000,0000,0000,,He's picking something up.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:13.20,0:11:16.15,DCMain,GENTA,0000,0000,0000,,Isn't that the Higo-san strap?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:16.38,0:11:18.47,DCMain,MITSUHIKO,0000,0000,0000,,You're right. It looks like it.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:18.47,0:11:20.19,DCMain,AYUMI,0000,0000,0000,,That must be it.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:20.19,0:11:24.71,DCMain,AGASA,0000,0000,0000,,Then maybe he delivered it to \Nthe station's lost and found.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:24.71,0:11:25.91,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Call them right away.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:26.13,0:11:26.91,DCMain,AGASA,0000,0000,0000,,Got it.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:27.09,0:11:28.46,DCMain,AGASA,0000,0000,0000,,For Ai-kun.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:30.18,0:11:32.17,DCMain,AGASA,0000,0000,0000,,What? You have it?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:32.55,0:11:36.50,DCMain,AGASA,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, it's a phone strap of a soccer player.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:37.05,0:11:38.33,DCMain,AGASA,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, that's it.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:38.33,0:11:41.23,DCMain,AGASA,0000,0000,0000,,We'll come by later to pick it up.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:41.23,0:11:42.43,DCMain,ALL,0000,0000,0000,,All right!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:42.61,0:11:44.77,DCMain,AYUMI,0000,0000,0000,,Ai-chan, they have it!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:45.20,0:11:47.93,DCMain,MITSUHIKO,0000,0000,0000,,She's still dazed.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:48.69,0:11:49.68,DCMain,GENTA,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:51.30,0:11:54.06,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,We'll go to Beika Station to pick it up.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:54.67,0:11:55.59,DCMain,ALL,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:55.59,0:11:56.98,DCMain,AGASA,0000,0000,0000,,Wait, wait.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:57.32,0:11:58.20,DCMain,ALL,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:58.20,0:12:01.49,DCMain,AGASA,0000,0000,0000,,It's at the station in Chiyari City.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:01.81,0:12:03.49,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Chiyari City?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:03.76,0:12:06.29,DCMain,MITSUHIKO,0000,0000,0000,,Isn't that pretty far away?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:06.29,0:12:07.08,DCMain,AYUMI,0000,0000,0000,,What should we do?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:07.08,0:12:08.67,DCMain,GENTA,0000,0000,0000,,I'm out of money.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:08.67,0:12:11.75,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,My turbo-powered skateboard \Nis being repaired.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:12.11,0:12:14.48,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Professor, could you drive \Nus there in your Beetle?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:14.48,0:12:15.44,DCMain,GENTA,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:15.44,0:12:16.72,DCMain,MITSUHIKO,0000,0000,0000,,Please!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:16.72,0:12:20.94,DCMain,AGASA,0000,0000,0000,,My bartender friend's borrowing it.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:20.94,0:12:22.52,DCMain,ALL,0000,0000,0000,,No way...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:22.52,0:12:26.39,DCMain,AGASA,0000,0000,0000,,There's no rush. You can go get it tomorrow.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:28.04,0:12:31.02,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,In that case, I'll run there.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:31.21,0:12:32.91,DCMain,GENTA,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:32.91,0:12:34.77,DCMain,MITSUHIKO,0000,0000,0000,,But it's tens of kilometers away!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:36.54,0:12:37.15,DCMain,OKIYA,0000,0000,0000,,Oh?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:38.80,0:12:40.68,DCMain,OKIYA,0000,0000,0000,,Is something the matter?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:40.68,0:12:42.03,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Subaru-san!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:42.24,0:12:46.52,DCMain,OKIYA,0000,0000,0000,,Since I was told I hadn't stewed \Nmy curry long enough the other day,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:46.52,0:12:50.29,DCMain,OKIYA,0000,0000,0000,,I brought a new batch to share.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:50.58,0:12:51.62,DCMain,MITSUHIKO,0000,0000,0000,,More importantly,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:51.62,0:12:56.38,DCMain,MITSUHIKO,0000,0000,0000,,Haibara-san's very important phone \Nstrap was taken to Chiyari Station.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:56.38,0:12:58.76,DCMain,AYUMI,0000,0000,0000,,We're on our way to get it right now.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:58.76,0:13:01.69,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Could you drive us there?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:01.69,0:13:03.05,DCMain,OKIYA,0000,0000,0000,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:04.82,0:13:06.75,DCMain,OKIYA,0000,0000,0000,,She's not going?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:06.75,0:13:09.74,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,No. She's pretty shocked \Nabout the whole thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:11.39,0:13:15.73,DCMain,OKIYA,0000,0000,0000,,Unfortunately, I need to \Nuse my car after this.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:15.88,0:13:17.32,DCMain,ALL,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:17.32,0:13:18.40,DCMain,MITSUHIKO,0000,0000,0000,,You can't take us?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:18.76,0:13:23.01,DCMain,OKIYA,0000,0000,0000,,But I saw a familiar car \Nparked next to this house.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:23.01,0:13:24.88,DCMain,OKIYA,0000,0000,0000,,Why don't you ask him?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:24.88,0:13:26.33,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,A familiar car?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:27.09,0:13:30.33,DCMain,OKIYA,0000,0000,0000,,A white RX-7.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:38.29,0:13:39.75,DCMain,AYUMI,0000,0000,0000,,I knew it!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:40.07,0:13:41.79,DCMain,AYUMI,0000,0000,0000,,It's Amuro-san!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:41.79,0:13:44.17,DCMain,MITSUHIKO,0000,0000,0000,,What are you doing here?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:44.17,0:13:49.14,DCMain,AMURO,0000,0000,0000,,I got sleepy while driving \Nin the area, so I took a nap.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:49.74,0:13:52.13,DCMain,AMURO,0000,0000,0000,,What are you kids doing?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:52.13,0:13:57.60,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,We're going to Chiyari Station to pick \Nup the phone strap our friend dropped.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:58.11,0:13:59.77,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Could you drive us there?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:00.01,0:14:01.36,DCMain,ALL,0000,0000,0000,,Please!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:02.95,0:14:06.87,DCMain,OKIYA,0000,0000,0000,,I'd also like to ask that you do this.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:07.45,0:14:11.27,DCMain,OKIYA,0000,0000,0000,,Though if there's some reason you \Ndon't want to leave this place,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:12.01,0:14:13.85,DCMain,OKIYA,0000,0000,0000,,then I suppose it can't be helped.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:14.52,0:14:19.50,DCMain,AMURO,0000,0000,0000,,I wanted to nap a little \Nlonger, but that's too bad.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:20.08,0:14:23.59,DCMain,AMURO,0000,0000,0000,,This is a thrillingly good place to nap.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:24.31,0:14:27.26,LostandFound,SIGN,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(335,1)}Toto Metro Lost and Found
Dialogue: 0,0:14:25.26,0:14:26.93,DCMain,EMPLOYEE,0000,0000,0000,,Thanks for waiting, kids.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:27.89,0:14:29.97,DCMain,EMPLOYEE,0000,0000,0000,,Here. This is the strap, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:31.23,0:14:31.97,DCMain,AYUMI,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:32.31,0:14:33.70,DCMain,AYUMI,0000,0000,0000,,That's not it!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:33.70,0:14:35.79,DCMain,GENTA,0000,0000,0000,,That's Sanada!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:35.79,0:14:38.48,DCMain,MITSUHIKO,0000,0000,0000,,We lost a Higo strap!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:38.81,0:14:40.84,DCMain,EMPLOYEE,0000,0000,0000,,What? This isn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:41.47,0:14:45.78,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Was this the man who turned that in?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:47.28,0:14:50.49,DCMain,EMPLOYEE,0000,0000,0000,,No, it was a younger man.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:51.59,0:14:53.74,DCMain,MITSUHIKO,0000,0000,0000,,What's going on?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:53.74,0:14:55.39,DCMain,AMURO,0000,0000,0000,,Maybe...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:56.25,0:14:57.50,DCMain,AMURO,0000,0000,0000,,Could I see that?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:58.36,0:15:04.12,DCMain,AMURO,0000,0000,0000,,This man in the photo appears to be the \Nfather of the boy standing next to him.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:04.77,0:15:08.34,DCMain,AMURO,0000,0000,0000,,Maybe he mistook the Higo \Nstrap your friend dropped
Dialogue: 0,0:15:08.34,0:15:12.06,DCMain,AMURO,0000,0000,0000,,for the Sanada strap his son dropped
Dialogue: 0,0:15:12.06,0:15:14.26,DCMain,AMURO,0000,0000,0000,,and picked up yours.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:14.79,0:15:20.49,DCMain,AMURO,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}Unless you're a passionate fan, \Nthey probably all look the same.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:16.81,0:15:20.77,HigoSanada,TEXT,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(231,1)}Higo     Sanada
Dialogue: 0,0:15:21.05,0:15:25.04,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,In other words, someone picked up \Nthe Sanada strap his son dropped
Dialogue: 0,0:15:25.04,0:15:28.08,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,and turned it in here.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:28.08,0:15:32.08,DCMain,MITSUHIKO,0000,0000,0000,,Then we need to find the father \Nand son recorded by my phone.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:32.08,0:15:33.94,DCMain,AYUMI,0000,0000,0000,,But how are we going to find them?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:33.94,0:15:36.21,DCMain,GENTA,0000,0000,0000,,We don't even know their names.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:36.21,0:15:37.56,DCMain,MITSUHIKO,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:37.56,0:15:42.01,DCMain,AMURO,0000,0000,0000,,Why don't we think about that \Nonce we return to my car?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:42.01,0:15:43.75,DCMain,ALL,0000,0000,0000,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:47.99,0:15:50.01,DCMain,GENTA,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, right.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:50.59,0:15:51.88,DCMain,GENTA,0000,0000,0000,,Excuse me!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:51.88,0:15:52.76,DCMain,EMPLOYEE,0000,0000,0000,,Yes?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:52.91,0:15:57.09,DCMain,GENTA,0000,0000,0000,,Was a badge turned in along with that strap?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:57.09,0:16:00.41,DCMain,EMPLOYEE,0000,0000,0000,,A badge? No, I don't think so.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:00.41,0:16:01.60,DCMain,GENTA,0000,0000,0000,,I see...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:02.20,0:16:03.58,DCMain,GENTA,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:05.31,0:16:07.99,DCMain,MITSUHIKO,0000,0000,0000,,Genta-kun, what are you doing?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:08.60,0:16:09.28,DCMain,GENTA,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:09.69,0:16:14.28,DCMain,GENTA,0000,0000,0000,,I lost my Detective Badge on the train, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:14.69,0:16:16.25,DCMain,AMURO,0000,0000,0000,,Your Detective Badge?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:16.25,0:16:18.33,DCMain,AYUMI,0000,0000,0000,,The professor made them for us.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:18.91,0:16:20.54,DCMain,MITSUHIKO,0000,0000,0000,,We all have them.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:27.66,0:16:31.05,DCMain,AMURO,0000,0000,0000,,Now then, how should we \Nfind this man with his son
Dialogue: 0,0:16:31.99,0:16:35.08,DCMain,AMURO,0000,0000,0000,,who picked up the Higo strap
Dialogue: 0,0:16:35.08,0:16:39.70,DCMain,AMURO,0000,0000,0000,,your friend dropped on the train?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:40.90,0:16:45.56,DCMain,AMURO,0000,0000,0000,,Both of them look very tan.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:45.56,0:16:46.87,DCMain,AYUMI,0000,0000,0000,,You're right.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:46.87,0:16:48.31,DCMain,GENTA,0000,0000,0000,,They're so dark.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:48.81,0:16:54.20,DCMain,MITSUHIKO,0000,0000,0000,,Maybe... They're on their way \Nto go swimming at the beach.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:54.53,0:16:56.73,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,No, that's not it.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:57.38,0:16:58.81,DCMain,MITSUHIKO,0000,0000,0000,,Why not?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:58.81,0:17:03.31,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,This video was taken while \Nwe were on the train
Dialogue: 0,0:17:03.31,0:17:05.32,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,after the soccer game that ended at 3 PM.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:05.32,0:17:08.62,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,We arrived at Beika Station \Nten minutes after that,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:08.62,0:17:12.18,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,so if they were going swimming, \Nthey would've left earlier.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:12.18,0:17:13.47,DCMain,MITSUHIKO,0000,0000,0000,,You're right.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:14.38,0:17:17.59,DCMain,AYUMI,0000,0000,0000,,Then maybe they're on their \Nway back from the beach.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:17.59,0:17:19.12,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,That's not it either.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:19.12,0:17:19.72,DCMain,AYUMI,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:20.09,0:17:23.31,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,We were riding the Shonan Shinjuku train.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:23.06,0:17:34.49,map 4,TEXT,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(440,1)}Takasaki\N\N\NOmiya\NShinjuku\NOdawara | Yokohama | Beika\NOfuna
Dialogue: 0,0:17:24.00,0:17:26.76,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,It departs from Takasaki in Gunma \Nand passes through Shinjuku
Dialogue: 0,0:17:26.76,0:17:31.71,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,and Yokohama on its way \Nto Odawara in Kanagawa.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:32.13,0:17:34.49,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,And the beach doesn't reach Beika Station.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:34.85,0:17:36.79,DCMain,AYUMI,0000,0000,0000,,Maybe they went to an indoor pool.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:36.79,0:17:38.43,DCMain,GENTA,0000,0000,0000,,Or bug hunting.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:38.43,0:17:41.74,DCMain,MITSUHIKO,0000,0000,0000,,Or maybe they just went to \Nan acquaintance's house.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:43.94,0:17:48.79,DCMain,AMURO,0000,0000,0000,,In that case, did you overhear \Nany of their conversation?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:49.06,0:17:50.73,DCMain,MITSUHIKO,0000,0000,0000,,Their conversation?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:51.18,0:17:56.26,DCMain,GENTA,0000,0000,0000,,I was bragging about how I polished my badge.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:56.79,0:17:57.93,DCMain,AYUMI,0000,0000,0000,,Come to think of it,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:58.15,0:17:59.90,DCMain,AYUMI,0000,0000,0000,,the dad said to his son,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:59.90,0:18:03.17,DCMain,AYUMI,0000,0000,0000,,“It's about as long as it \Ntakes to watch {\i1}Kamen Yaiba{\i0}.”
Dialogue: 0,0:18:03.86,0:18:06.62,DCMain,AYUMI,0000,0000,0000,,But {\i1}Kamen Yaiba{\i0} wasn't on today.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:06.62,0:18:08.19,DCMain,GENTA,0000,0000,0000,,Isn't it on tomorrow?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:09.65,0:18:13.93,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Before his father said \Nthat, did the boy ask him,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:14.36,0:18:16.07,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,“How much longer?”
Dialogue: 0,0:18:16.81,0:18:18.70,DCMain,AYUMI,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, he did.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:20.21,0:18:25.04,DCMain,AMURO,0000,0000,0000,,Which means it's possible he was using \Nthe thirty minute {\i1}Kamen Yaiba{\i0} program
Dialogue: 0,0:18:25.04,0:18:29.23,DCMain,AMURO,0000,0000,0000,,to explain to his son how much longer it \Nwould take to arrive at their destination.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:29.23,0:18:30.46,DCMain,AYUMI,0000,0000,0000,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:30.93,0:18:33.83,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Do you know when they said that?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:33.83,0:18:34.86,DCMain,AYUMI,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:34.86,0:18:39.97,DCMain,AYUMI,0000,0000,0000,,It was after the train screeched \Nto a stop and everyone fell.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:39.97,0:18:46.98,map 4 - Copy,TEXT,0000,0000,0000,,Shinjuku\NBeika\N\NYokohama\NChiyari\NOfuna
Dialogue: 0,0:18:40.37,0:18:44.34,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,So it's 30 minutes from Beika Station.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:44.94,0:18:46.98,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,That's here around Chiyari Station.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:47.20,0:18:52.00,DCMain,MITSUHIKO,0000,0000,0000,,That boy seemed to be a first-year \Nelementary school student like us.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:52.00,0:18:55.87,DCMain,MITSUHIKO,0000,0000,0000,,It's not unreasonable that his father \Nwould use Yaiba as an example.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:56.26,0:18:59.18,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,How do you know he's a first-year?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:59.18,0:19:03.95,DCMain,MITSUHIKO,0000,0000,0000,,Because he breathed on the train window
Dialogue: 0,0:19:03.95,0:19:07.07,DCMain,MITSUHIKO,0000,0000,0000,,and wrote something with his finger.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:08.15,0:19:12.25,DCMain,MITSUHIKO,0000,0000,0000,,He said, “It's only hiragana, but I \Ncan write it now. Aren't you proud?”
Dialogue: 0,0:19:12.79,0:19:15.84,DCMain,MITSUHIKO,0000,0000,0000,,I think he was writing his own name.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:16.40,0:19:19.88,DCMain,MITSUHIKO,0000,0000,0000,,Unfortunately, I couldn't see what he wrote.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:20.31,0:19:24.16,DCMain,AMURO,0000,0000,0000,,Do you remember which car you were riding in?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:24.16,0:19:27.93,DCMain,GENTA,0000,0000,0000,,We got on in the middle of the \Nthird car from the front, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:27.93,0:19:29.02,DCMain,MITSUHIKO,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:30.77,0:19:34.15,DCMain,AYUMI,0000,0000,0000,,You really don't remember what he wrote?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:34.15,0:19:34.90,DCMain,MITSUHIKO,0000,0000,0000,,No.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:35.33,0:19:39.53,DCMain,MITSUHIKO,0000,0000,0000,,I do remember his pale finger \Npressed against the window though.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:39.74,0:19:41.57,DCMain,GENTA,0000,0000,0000,,Pale finger?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:41.84,0:19:45.11,DCMain,GENTA,0000,0000,0000,,They're both really dark from being so tan.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:45.11,0:19:48.29,DCMain,MITSUHIKO,0000,0000,0000,,But if you look closely at the video...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:48.76,0:19:50.82,DCMain,MITSUHIKO,0000,0000,0000,,See? It's both of them.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:52.60,0:19:58.42,DCMain,GENTA,0000,0000,0000,,They're both pale from the wrist down!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:59.00,0:20:02.43,DCMain,AYUMI,0000,0000,0000,,And look at the dad's bag.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:02.82,0:20:05.85,DCMain,AYUMI,0000,0000,0000,,It looks like there's \Nsomething angular inside it.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:06.61,0:20:10.93,DCMain,MITSUHIKO,0000,0000,0000,,Maybe he put his cooler inside \Nhis bag since the strap broke.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:10.93,0:20:13.01,DCMain,AYUMI,0000,0000,0000,,Are they going fishing?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:13.01,0:20:15.31,DCMain,GENTA,0000,0000,0000,,But they don't have fishing rods.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:15.31,0:20:18.46,DCMain,MITSUHIKO,0000,0000,0000,,And they're too lightly dressed to go hiking.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:18.95,0:20:20.24,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Maybe...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:20.74,0:20:22.09,DCMain,ALL,0000,0000,0000,,Maybe?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:22.09,0:20:24.70,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,They could be digging for clams.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:24.70,0:20:25.72,DCMain,BOTH,0000,0000,0000,,Dig...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:25.72,0:20:27.26,DCMain,MITSUHIKO,0000,0000,0000,,Digging for clams?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:28.95,0:20:31.13,DCMain,AYUMI,0000,0000,0000,,You go digging for clams in spring!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:31.13,0:20:32.93,DCMain,GENTA,0000,0000,0000,,We're on summer break!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:32.93,0:20:36.78,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Actually, you can do it all year round.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:36.78,0:20:39.60,DCMain,ALL,0000,0000,0000,,What? Really?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:39.60,0:20:40.46,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:40.77,0:20:46.33,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,April to May is the best season \Nbecause the climate means
Dialogue: 0,0:20:46.33,0:20:49.16,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,the clams are full of \Nnutrients from spawning,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:49.06,0:20:54.98,map 1,TEXT,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(438,1)}Yokohama\NYokosuka\NOdawara\NMiura\NIto
Dialogue: 0,0:20:49.06,0:20:54.98,map 2,TEXT,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(438,1)}Oarai\NTokyo | Chiba | Choshi Port
Dialogue: 0,0:20:49.06,0:20:54.98,map 3,TEXT,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(438,1)}Katsuura\NMera
Dialogue: 0,0:20:49.70,0:20:54.98,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,but there are plenty of beaches that are \Nopen to digging for clams as late as July.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:55.57,0:21:01.23,DCMain,AMURO,0000,0000,0000,,And low tide at Chiyari \NBeach is at 5:59 today.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:01.64,0:21:06.89,DCMain,AMURO,0000,0000,0000,,When digging for clams, it's best to \Narrive an hour or two before low tide,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:07.34,0:21:10.03,DCMain,AMURO,0000,0000,0000,,so it makes sense that they took that train.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:10.35,0:21:12.54,DCMain,AYUMI,0000,0000,0000,,Really? Then...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:12.54,0:21:14.58,DCMain,GENTA,0000,0000,0000,,If we go to that beach...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:14.58,0:21:17.54,DCMain,MITSUHIKO,0000,0000,0000,,We'll be able to retrieve \NHaibara-san's strap!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:18.02,0:21:23.02,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Once that boy realizes the strap \Nhis dad picked up isn't his,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:23.02,0:21:24.42,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sure he'll hand it over.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:24.85,0:21:25.92,DCMain,AYUMI,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:25.92,0:21:28.70,DCMain,AYUMI,0000,0000,0000,,And once we get it,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:28.70,0:21:32.10,DCMain,AYUMI,0000,0000,0000,,we won't let anyone else take it \Nuntil we return it to Ai-chan!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:32.60,0:21:34.34,DCMain,AYUMI,0000,0000,0000,,No matter what!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:34.80,0:21:36.02,DCMain,GENTA,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:36.02,0:21:39.11,DCMain,MITSUHIKO,0000,0000,0000,,Yes! Haibara-san will be so happy!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:39.91,0:21:41.11,DCMain,GENTA,0000,0000,0000,,This is great!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:41.11,0:21:44.03,DCMain,MITSUHIKO,0000,0000,0000,,Yes! I'm so happy!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:45.13,0:21:47.49,DCMain,AMURO,0000,0000,0000,,I'll go settle the bill.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:47.91,0:21:50.58,DCMain,AMURO,0000,0000,0000,,You kids head to the car.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:51.06,0:21:51.81,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Sure.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:52.83,0:21:55.20,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Thanks, Amuro-san.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:55.57,0:21:57.71,DCMain,ALL,0000,0000,0000,,Thanks for the food!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:17.57,0:22:18.61,DCMain,AMURO,0000,0000,0000,,Kazami?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:45.02,0:24:09.05,DCEpPreview,TEXT,0000,0000,0000,,Episode Preview
Dialogue: 0,0:23:45.30,0:23:51.05,DCMain,OKIYA,0000,0000,0000,,She's in that state because \Nshe lost her Higo strap?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:51.72,0:23:52.32,DCMain,AGASA,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:52.74,0:23:56.45,DCMain,OKIYA,0000,0000,0000,,It's less likely that it won't be found.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:56.92,0:24:00.83,DCMain,OKIYA,0000,0000,0000,,Japan's top two inspectors are on the case.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:01.30,0:24:02.86,DCItalic,AMURO,0000,0000,0000,,Breathe on it.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:02.86,0:24:03.54,DCMain,KAZAMI,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:03.94,0:24:05.79,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Nice one, Amuro-san.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:05.79,0:24:07.80,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Now that we know that...
Dialogue: 0,0:24:09.05,0:24:15.05,DCNextEp,TEXT,0000,0000,0000,,The Heartfelt Strap \N(Part Two)
Dialogue: 0,0:24:09.50,0:24:14.57,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,The next episode of Conan is \N“The Heartfelt Strap, Part Two!”
Dialogue: 0,0:24:30.07,0:24:34.99,Hint,TEXT,0000,0000,0000,,Haibara's Strap
Dialogue: 0,0:24:30.82,0:24:32.99,DCMain,HAIBARA,0000,0000,0000,,Next Conan's hint.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:32.99,0:24:34.68,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Haibara's strap!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:34.99,0:24:39.99,Don'tMiss,TEXT,0000,0000,0000,,Don't miss the next episode.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:35.22,0:24:36.49,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}Amuro-san, thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:36.49,0:24:39.20,DCMain,AMURO,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}With you, looking for lost objects \Nbecomes a profound experience.
